{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"safe","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"index","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Index","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Element","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa"},{"text":"? { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"index","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The position of the element to access."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the index is within the bounds of the collection, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"the element at that position is returned. Otherwise, "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The element at the specified index if it is within the collection’s bounds; otherwise, "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This subscript provides a safe way to access elements within the collection by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of crashing when accessing an index out of bounds."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is useful for avoiding runtime errors when the exact count of the collection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"might not be known or when dealing with dynamic data sources."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This approach ensures that attempts to access indices outside the valid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"range simply result in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing for more graceful handling of such cases."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Example usage:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]","if let number = numbers[safe: 3] {","    print(number) \/\/ Prints \"4\"","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\")","}","","if let outOfBoundsNumber = numbers[safe: 10] {","    print(outOfBoundsNumber)","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\") \/\/ Prints \"Index out of bounds\"","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method enhances the safety and readability of collection access, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"especially in more complex logic where bounds checks are necessary."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection\/subscript(safe:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:Sl11SwiftExtrasE4safe7ElementQzSg5IndexQz_tcip","extendedModule":"Swift","modules":[{"name":"SwiftExtras","relatedModules":["Swift"]}],"conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Available when"}],"constraints":[{"code":"Self","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"Collection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"conform